WEBVTT

00:02:59.196 --> 00:03:01.379
"Yeah, you did a great job
in this one task,

00:03:01.403 --> 00:03:05.205
but what we really need to talk about
are your areas for improvement."

00:03:06.284 --> 00:03:08.601
Psychologists have found
that for many of us,

00:03:08.625 --> 00:03:10.958
bad tends to loom larger than good.

00:03:11.379 --> 00:03:13.748
So your boss tells you
you have a weakness,

00:03:13.772 --> 00:03:16.401
and -- boom! -- that's all
you can think about.

00:03:17.190 --> 00:03:19.537
And this starts
long before you have a job.

00:03:19.561 --> 00:03:22.205
Marcus Buckingham: Beginning
very early, in kindergarten

00:03:22.229 --> 00:03:24.814
all the way up through school
and college and so forth

00:03:24.838 --> 00:03:26.666
and then perpetuated in the workplace.

00:03:26.690 --> 00:03:29.062
AG: Marcus Buckingham
is an author and consultant.

